  "text": "Naumann [CITATION_1] proposes a notion of purity that is more liberal than JML's weak purity and allows certain modifications of existing objects, for instance, updates of encapsulated caches. Extending our approach to this notion of purity is possible by weakening the relation such that modifications of invisible fields are permitted.",
